This archive provides the implementation of the Channel Data Exchange (CDX) library.

Compilation
===========

To compile the library, run

  autoreconf -i
  ./configure CXXFLAGS=-I/usr/include/hdf5/serial LDFLAGS=-L/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/hdf5/serial

The Debian packages devscripts and dh-autoreconf are needed to build this package.

These commands generate a Debian package:

 mkdir -p ~/packaging/libcdx && \
 cp -r ~/workspace/cdx/trunk/CPP ~/packaging/libcdx/libcdx_1.0 && \
 cd ~/packaging/libcdx && \
 tar cfz libcdx_1.0.orig.tar.gz libcdx_1.0 && \
 cd libcdx_1.0 && \
 DEB_BUILD_OPTIONS="parallel=4" nice debuild -us -uc

Installation on Mac OS X
========================

In snacs/cdx_format/CPP run

  ./configure CXXFLAGS=-I/opt/local/include LDFLAGS=-L/opt/local/lib --prefix=/opt/local
  make
  sudo make install

In snacs/cdx_format/python run
  sudo /opt/local/bin/python2 setup.py install

In snacs/cdx_format/tools run
